    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA170-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi viṟalikku vāyiṉ maṟuttatu. (missing in G1+2)</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante refused the mediation of the dancing girl.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA170">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            maṭakkaṇ ṭakarak kūntaṟ paṇaittōḷ</l>
<l>            vārnta vāleyiṟṟuc cērntuceṟi kuṟaṅkiṟ</l>
<l>            piṇaiya lantaḻai tataiit tuṇaiyilaḷ</l>
<l>            viḻavukkaḷam poliya vantuniṉ ṟaṉaḷē</l>
<l>            yeḻumiṉō veḻumiṉaṅ koḻunaṟ kākka </l>
<l>            māriyar tuvaṉṟiya pēricai muḷḷūrp</l>
<l>            palaruṭaṉ kaḻitta voḷvāṇ malaiyaṉa</l>
<l>            toruvēṟ kōṭi yāṅkunam</l>
<l>            paṉmaiya tevaṉōviva ṇaṉmaitalaip paṭiṉē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent3">Modest eyes, anointed tresses, bamboo shoulders,</l>
<l rend="indent3">with upright pure teeth, with thighs joined close together(?),<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">cērntuceṟi</term>: does this mean more than being close?</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">gathering pretty foliage in [her] garland,</l>
<l rend="indent4">she without companion,</l>
<l>she came [and] stood for the festival floor to glitter.</l>
<l>Rise, let’s rise to protect [our] husband!</l>
<l rend="indent3">If [he] meets her beauty(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">naṉmai</term> here certainly refers to the rival woman's physical qualities, but what is the precise social and emotional impact? Irony or the sincere feeling of being inferior?</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent4">what of our being many,</l>
<l rend="indent2">like [those who] ran from the one spear</l>
<l rend="indent2">of Malaiyaṉ with bright sword who did away with many together</l>
<l rend="indent3">in famous Muḷḷūr filled by Āriyar?</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
